I (17F) ((18 in a week party) recently was just diagnosed, and although everything seems to all makes sense the more more I read, I feel like it would be extremely beneficial for me to have a friend that is diagnosed as well. To give context to this, I live in a town that has less than 4000 people, and when it comes to mental illness, they are all stuck in the 1920s. It’s gotten to the point where I’ve exhausted my mother and my brother (my main support network besides healthcare providers) with me venting or stressing out or having a spiral. They aren’t quite equipped to giving advice on the subject, and don’t quite have the tolerance to lend an ear/shoulder.

All I’m hoping to gain is just somebody that I can talk to without feeling like I’m constantly judged or annoying them about day-to-day struggles, and hopefully that person can open up to me with the same.

I don’t mind if they are new to this whole thing as well, I just don’t want to feel alone any more

My BPD is very much anxiety/depression based

I would love to join something like this!
